summary: An Ordinance appropriating the additional sum of Forty-five and 85/100 ($45.85) Dollars, or so much thereof as may be necessary out of the General Fund in favor of Keystone Place Condemnation Fund authorized by Ordinance No. 14029, approved July 17, 1906, providing for the laying off, extending and establishing of Keystone Place for the purpose of paying accrued interest on outstanding warrants in said district.
